<topic id="how_to_postgresql">
  <title>Configuring a PostgreSQL Database Connection</title>
  <body>
    <p>To configure the support for a PostgreSQL database, follow this procedure:<ol>
        <li><ph
            conref="download-database-drivers.dita#download-database-drivers/postgresql-download-driver"
          /></li>
        <li><xref
            href="../tasks/configure-postgreSQL-datasource.dita#configure-postgreSQL-datasource"
            >Configure PostgreSQL <term>Data Source</term> drivers</xref>.</li>
        <li><xref
            href="../tasks/configure-postgreSQL-connection.dita#configure-postgreSQL-connection"
            >Configure a PostgreSQL <term>Connection</term></xref>.</li>
        <li>To view your connection, go to the <uicontrol>Data Source Explorer</uicontrol> view <ph
            conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/reopen-view-parenthesis"/> or switch to the
            <uicontrol>Database Perspective</uicontrol> (available from <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Open Perspective</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Database</uicontrol>
          </menucascade>).</li>
      </ol></p>
  </body>
